choices.text:
Put together a healthy meal plan for me for this week.  I can't have dairy, garlic, honey, almonds, pistachios, or cashews
Monday:
- Breakfast: Oatmeal with fruit and nuts (excluding almonds, pistachios, and cashews)
- Lunch: Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens and vegetables 
- Dinner: Baked salmon with roasted sweet potatoes and steamed broccoli
Tuesday:
- Breakfast: Smoothie bowl made with fruit, yogurt substitute (excluding dairy), and granola (excluding almonds)
- Lunch: Turkey lettuce wraps with avocado and tomato 
- Dinner: Quinoa stuffed bell peppers with roasted vegetables
Wednesday:
- Breakfast: Scrambled eggs with spinach and mushrooms (excluding garlic)
- Lunch: Grilled tofu stir fry with mixed veggies and brown rice 
- Dinner: Baked chicken breast with steamed asparagus and sweet potato wedges
Thursday:
- Breakfast: Greek yogurt parfait made with fruit and granola (excluding almonds)
- Lunch: Grilled shrimp skewers with mixed veggies 
- Dinner: Baked salmon with roasted sweet potatoes and steamed broccoli
